<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669765>
    dc:description "FIGURE 19. Egg capsules of Scyliorhinus species. A, S. canicula, AMNH 4121 (Naples, Italy); B, S. capensis, SAIAB 6286 (Algoa Bay, South Africa); C, S. retifer, AMNH 15611 (United States). Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669855>
    dc:description "FIGURE 63. Holotype of Scyliorhinus retifer (Garman, 1881), MCZ 825, male, 311 mm TL (Delaware, United States). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669855/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669857>
    dc:description "FIGURE 64. Scyliorhinus retifer; dorsal view. A, USNM 221510, female, 402 mm TL (no locality data); B, UF 27984, female, 435 mm TL (Gulf of Mexico, 28°41’N, 86°26’W); C, UF 185085, female, 449 mm TL (Gulf of Mexico, 29°26.24’N, 87°34.24’W). Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669857/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669859>
    dc:description "FIGURE 65. Scyliorhinus retifer. A, UF 36359, female, 353 mm TL; B–E, UF 36359, male, 372 mm TL (Virginia, United States, 36°30’N, 74°45’W); F, UF 101261, male, 242 mm TL (Gulf of Mexico, 24°11’N, 83°31’W). A, B, ventral view of head; C, detail of pectoral fins; D, lateral view of head; E, dorsal view of head; F, detail of pelvic fins and claspers. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669859/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669861>
    dc:description "FIGURE 66. Teeth of Scyliorhinus retifer; labial view, UF 36359, male, 372 mm TL (Virginia, United States, 36°30’N, 74°45’W). a, anterior tooth; c, commissural; l, lateral; ps, parassymphysial. Scale bar = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669861/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669863>
    dc:description "FIGURE 67. Dermal denticles of Scyliorhinus retifer. A–C, UF 28525, female, 500 mm TL (Mexico, 20°43’N, 92°25.8’W); D–F, UF 36359, male, 372 mm TL (Virginia, United States, 36°30’N, 74°45’W). A, D, region above pectoral fin base; B, E, region below first dorsal fin origin; C, F, region below second dorsal fin insertion. Scale bar = 250 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669863/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669865>
    dc:description "FIGURE 68. Clasper of Scyliorhinus retifer: dorsal view, UF 36359, 372 mm TL (Virginia, United States, 36°30’N, 74°45’W). A, external morphology; B, skeleton. crh, rhipidion cover; end, endstyle; en, envelope; erh, exorhipidion; hp, hipopyle; rd, dorsal marginal cartilage; rh, rhipidion; rv, ventral marginal cartilage; t3, terminal 3 cartilage; td, dorsal terminal cartilage; td2, dorsal terminal 2 cartilage; tdc, terminal dermal cover; tv, ventral terminal cartilage; tv2, ventral terminal 2 cartilage. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669865/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669867>
    dc:description "FIGURE 69. Map showing the geographic distribution of Scyliorhinus retifer based on material examined in this study. Black star indicates the type locality." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669867/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

